	   <a name=100121442235088></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100121442235088><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100121442235088>Solo tactics</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100121442235088#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Sat, Sep 22nd 11:07 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Whenever I solo in OT, I get about a half a blue, which is awesome.....When I live..... The problem is I'll malise, then send my water pet in.&nbsp;&nbsp;I'll sit and wait till waterpet gets like 75% health, then nuke once or twice.  Problem is, healing doesn't work well (on pet) chain summoning is costly, and I always seem to agro the mob way too easily (1 or two nukes in a row does it) but to kill I pretty much have to non-stop nuke...... any ideas?  Thanks!<br><br>Natakux Toymaker<br>31st lvl gnomish magician<br>E'CI<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>
<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%>
	   <a name=100231577521861></a>
	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100231577521861><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100231577521861>RE: Solo tactics</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100231577521861#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=96333><span id=Scholar>JBugman</span></a>, <span id=Scholar>Scholar</span><br><span id=notbold>79 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Fri, Oct 5th 5:02 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Decent<span id=notbold>[3.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>&nbsp;&nbsp;Make sure you have Fireshield on the pet (and you) and pull once with FireBolt.  Wait until the mob almost gets to you and sic the pet.  Wait a little for the pet to fight with the mob (either the pet smacks the mob or the mob smacks the pet and gets Fireshielded), and then nuke the mob once.  Avoid chain nuking the mob until it's at least 50% dead.<br>  If/when you over nuke the mob, take some hits (you're still Fireshielded) and wait for the pet to smack the mob around.  Once the mob reattacks the pet, sit down and wait a bit and renuke.  You'll probably only get agroe'd once; twice and you're nuking waaay too early.<br>  If the mob hits too hard, then heal the pet once (before it gets below 50%) and then renuke.<br><br>  If you pull two or more blues, see how the fight goes and don't be afraid of running like a little girl.  Over nuking two or more mobs and having one aggro you while the other spanks around your pet is an accident (and lost XP) waiting to happen.<br><br>Hope this helps,<br><br>Coddington<br>lvl 27 Mage<br>Terris-Thule<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
	   </form></table><ul>

