	   <tr><td colspan=2>Can't help you on where.<br><br>Oh how, find yourself a friendly Druid to team up with. My druid frequently partners with a mage, and we do very well together. The two classes make fine compliments, the druid can keep you and pet alive, and keep pet buffed. Then can either assist you with dd/dot/nuke, or melee with the pet. Druid can also control the number of mobs in a pull.<br><br>Try teaming with a chanter too. While they don't have healing to my knowledge they have equally good buffs imo, and excellent dots they can back you with. If you are in a zone with lots of wanders, they can keep them mezzed and even charm them to help. Or they can just pull and let their ani assist your pet with melee.<br><br>Also, what pets are you commonly using? Someone else can give you tips on best pets vs mobs at your level.<br><br>But my uncle says that the Druid/Mage team is probably one of the best there is. Oh,if you add into the group, then try to pull in a rogue. Backstab is a wonderful thing.<br><br>Brigyd<br>&nbsp;<br>"In waking a tiger, use a very long stick." -Mao Tse-Tung. Did he go to Stonebrunt too?</td></tr>
