	   <form action=http://www1.allakhazam.com/perl/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100018472312705><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100018472312705>RE: mage</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=12&mid=100018472312705#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <span id= >Anonymous</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Sep 11th 1:05 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Default<span id=notbold>[2.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I hope you are not trolling for sarcastic responses.&nbsp;&nbsp;As you have heard many times before, each type of pet is useful for a different situation.  Here is my personal experience.<br><br>Fire: Great for fighting multiple enemies, and for fighting green enemies.  Its enormous damage shield makes short work of them, and you do not run a great risk of the pet dying because the enemies are relatively easy.  Besides the damage shield, the Fire elemental is generally inferior to the Water one (less hit points, less Strength, identical Agility, identical Direct Damage spell).  This does not take into account the fact that the Fire elemental does a Fire-based DD spell while the Water elemental does a Cold-based DD spell.<br><br>Air: Used for fighting blue enemies.  Its stun spell is a great taunt and keeps the enemy off your back, while it is the best tank because it doesn't get hit often (While Earth has more hit points, Air will last longer).<br><br>Water: Used for fighting white to yellow enemies.  Its DD spell is not as great a taunt, and IMHO is not as useful as the Air Elemental's stun attack; however, it will connect a lot more often because the air elemental's stun attack will often bounce off a white or yellow enemy.  The Water elemental is also a good tank, although not as good as Air.<br><br>Earth: I have not used the Earth elemental much lately, although it is a good choice to use when grouped with other spellcasters simply for the sake of its Root spell.  As with the Air elemental's stun spell, the Root does not hold if the enemy is too strong.  Also, remember that a rooted mob fights until it dies, which is another disadvantage of the Earth pet.  If you use the Earth pet for its Root spell, make sure to pull it back before it runs up to the enemy, because as long as the enemy is hitting your pet, you cannot tell it to back off.  It has the most hit points, but it is not the best tank, because its inferior Agility means that it gets hit a lot and generally doesn't last as long as the Air pet.  I would appreciate it if you give me a clear situation in which the Earth elemental is best.  Perhaps as a hybrid between Air and Fire, when you need a good tank, and deal a lot of damage with you Damage Shield at the same time.<br><br>Well, this was a long post - I hope that you found it helpful.<br><br>Rascarcapac, Level 30 Mage, Xev Server<br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
